webpackJsonp([0xe6bfc08803e5],{505:function(e,o){e.exports={pathContext:{docHtml:'<h1 id="workflow-notifications"><a href="#workflow-notifications" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Workflow Notifications</h1>\n<p>There are a number of use cases where you may wish to notify an external system when a workflow completes:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Send an email.</li>\n<li>Send a Slack (or other instant message).</li>\n<li>Send a message to Kafka (or other message bus).</li>\n</ol>\n<p>You have options:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>For individual workflows, can add an exit handler to your workflow, <a href="../examples/exit-handlers.yaml">for example</a>.</li>\n<li>If you want the same for every workflow, you can add an exit handler to <a href="default-workflow-specs.html">the default workflow spec</a>.</li>\n<li>Use a service (e.g. <a href="https://github.com/heptiolabs/eventrouter">Heptio Labs EventRouter</a>) to the <a href="workflow-events.html">Workflow events</a> we emit.</li>\n</ol>',docPath:"argo/workflow-notifications",proj:"argo"}}}});
